collections.name: Cyber Valley
collections.description:
NoName_Project is the origin of a Cyber Fantasy universe where technology and magic intertwine to create legendary stories.

The first universe in this saga is Cyber Valley, a realm torn apart by betrayal and ambition, leading to the rise of two warring factions:

Major Valley – A kingdom ruled by traitors who have built an artificial reality full of lies and control. They hold dominion over Geodesium, the most powerful mineral on the planet NoName, granting them unmatched technological supremacy.

Minor Valley – A rebellious republic, the last resistance against Major Valley’s oppression, fighting to restore truth and freedom.

However, this war extends beyond the two valleys. Other kingdoms, republics, and dictatorships rise in the shadows, each with their own interests: to destroy Major Valley’s rule and seize control of Geodesium to gain power. The battle is about to begin.

With this collection, we aim to raise funds to bring this project to life.

collections.name: Naturartistic
collections.description:
Naturartistic, the debut NFT collection from [Endy](https://naturartistic.com/about), an award-winning nature/fine art photographer. Masterfully crafted over the course of 18 years, it is composed of photographs in categories: Lotus and Waterlily(LW), Intimate Landscape(IL), Abstract/Detail(AD), Back and White(BW), Animal(A), Plant and Fungi(PF), showing the beauty and elegance nature. 

The numbering system: #1-ND-LW1-1/8

#1     =  NFT minting sequence no.1
ND    =  photographer initial for Endy
LW1  =  Lotus and Waterlily no.1 (category numbering)
1/8    =  1st of maximum 8 editions

collections.name: Ronin Rouge
collections.description:
“Ronin Rouge” is the latest collaboration between frequently sold-out Orangehare artists Yuki and Klara, where grace and danger are two sides of the same blade. Across 70 unique one-of-one pieces, the collection transforms the geisha into a warrior—elegant, poised, and undeniably lethal. Drawing from samurai cinema, Korean and Japanese woodblock traditions, and the bold energy of pop art, “Ronin Rouge” challenges the boundaries between beauty and brutality.

Designed and brought to life through Orangehare’s in-house production process, Yuki and Klara’s distinct styles merge into two sides of the same sword- because sometimes, the most dangerous disguise is elegance itself.
